6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to criminal procedure; granting
arrested persons the right to make telephone calls
8 within certain period of time; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 212 of Title 22, unless there is
14 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 Immediately upon being arrested and booked into a city or county
16 jail facility, and except where physically impossible, no later than
17 forty-eight (48) hours after arrest, an arrested person has the
18 right to make at least three completed telephone calls at no expense
19 if the calls are completed to telephone numbers within the local
20 calling area, or at his or her own expense if outside the local
21 calling area, to the following:
22 1. An attorney of his or her choice or, if he or she has no
23 funds to pay for an attorney of his or her choice, the public
24 defender, or other attorney assigned by the court to assist
